{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660cb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3056p"},"text":"§ 3056p.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions and rule","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660cc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this subchapter:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660cd-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Community service","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The term “community service” means—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660ce-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" social, health, welfare, and educational services (including literacy tutoring), legal and other counseling services and assistance, including tax counseling and assistance and financial counseling, and library, recreational, and other similar services;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660cf-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" conservation, maintenance, or restoration of natural resources;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660d0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" community betterment or beautification;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660d1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/1/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" antipollution and environmental quality efforts;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660d2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/1/E"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" weatherization activities;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660d3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/1/F"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"F"},"text":"(F)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" economic development; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660d4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/1/G"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"G"},"text":"(G)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" such other services essential and necessary to the community as the Secretary determines by rule to be appropriate.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660d5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Community service employment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “community service employment” means part-time, temporary employment paid with grant funds in projects described in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s3056/b/1/D"},"text":"section 3056(b)(1)(D) of this title","children":[],"tail":", through which eligible individuals are engaged in community service and receive work experience and job skills that can lead to unsubsidized employment."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660d6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Eligible individual","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660d7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “eligible individual” means an individual who is age 55 or older and who has a low income (including any such individual whose income is not more than 125 percent of the poverty line), excluding any income that is unemployment compensation, a benefit received under title XVI of the Social Security Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1381"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 1381","children":[],"tail":" et seq.), a payment made to or on behalf of veterans or former members of the Armed Forces under the laws administered by the Secretary of Veterans Affairs, or 25 percent of a benefit received under title II of the Social Security Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s401"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 401","children":[],"tail":" et seq.), subject to subsection (b)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660d8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Participation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660d9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/3/B/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Exclusion","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding any other provision of this paragraph, the term “eligible individual” does not include an individual who has participated in projects under this subchapter for a period of 48 months in the aggregate (whether or not consecutive) after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 2007","children":[],"tail":", unless the period was increased as described in clause (ii)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660da-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/3/B/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Increased periods of participation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall authorize a grantee for a project to increase the period of participation described in clause (i), pursuant to a request submitted by the grantee, for individuals who—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660db-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/3/B/ii/I"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"I"},"text":"(I)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" have a severe disability;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660dc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/3/B/ii/II"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"II"},"text":"(II)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" are frail or are age 75 or older;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660dd-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/3/B/ii/III"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"III"},"text":"(III)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" meet the eligibility requirements related to age for, but do not receive, benefits under title II of the Social Security Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s401"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 401","children":[],"tail":" et seq.);"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660de-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/3/B/ii/IV"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"IV"},"text":"(IV)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" live in an area with persistent unemployment and are individuals with severely limited employment prospects;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660df-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/3/B/ii/V"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"V"},"text":"(V)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" have limited English proficiency or low literacy skills; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660e0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/3/B/ii/VI"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"VI"},"text":"(VI)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" have been incarcerated within the last 5 years or are under supervision following release from prison or jail within the last 5 years.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660e1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Income","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In this section, the term “income” means income received during the 12-month period (or, at the option of the grantee involved, the annualized income for the 6-month period) ending on the date an eligible individual submits an application to participate in a project carried out under this subchapter by such grantee.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660e2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Local workforce development board; state workforce development board","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The terms “local workforce development board” and “State workforce development board” have the meanings given the terms “local board” and “State board”, respectively, in section 3 of the Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s3102"},"text":"29 U.S.C. 3102","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660e3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Pacific Island and Asian Americans","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “Pacific Island and Asian Americans” means Americans having origins in any of the original peoples of the Far East, Southeast Asia, the Indian Subcontinent, or the Pacific Islands.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660e4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Program","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “program” means the older American community service employment program established under this subchapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660e5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Supportive services","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “supportive services” means services, such as transportation, child care, dependent care, housing, and needs-related payments, that are necessary to enable an individual to participate in activities authorized under this subchapter, consistent with the provisions of this subchapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660e6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/a/9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9"},"text":"(9)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Unemployed","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “unemployed”, used with respect to a person or individual, means an individual who is without a job and who wants and is available for work, including an individual who may have occasional employment that does not result in a constant source of income.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660e7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Rule","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Pursuant to regulations prescribed by the Secretary, an eligible individual shall have priority for the community service employment and other authorized activities provided under this subchapter if the individual—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660e8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is 65 years of age or older; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660e9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660ea-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/b/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" has a disability;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660eb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/b/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" has limited English proficiency or low literacy skills;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660ec-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/b/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" resides in a rural area;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660ed-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/b/2/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is a veteran;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660ee-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/b/2/E"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" has low employment prospects;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660ef-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/b/2/F"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"F"},"text":"(F)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" has failed to find employment after utilizing services provided under title I of the Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s3111"},"text":"29 U.S.C. 3111","children":[],"tail":" et seq.];"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660f0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/b/2/G"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"G"},"text":"(G)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is homeless or at risk for homelessness; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660f1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s3056p/b/2/H"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"H"},"text":"(H)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" has been incarcerated within the last 5 years or is under supervision following release from prison or jail within the last 5 years.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbc6660f2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/73/tV/s518"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–73, title V, § 518","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/365/tV/s501"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–365, title V, § 501","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/2588"},"text":"120 Stat. 2588","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/128/tV/s512/w/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–128, title V, § 512(w)(8)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/1716"},"text":"128 Stat. 1716","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/144/s6/g"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–144, § 6(g)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-04-19"},"text":"Apr. 19, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/346"},"text":"130 Stat. 346","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/131/tIV/s401/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–131, title IV, § 401(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2020-03-25"},"text":"Mar. 25, 2020","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/266"},"text":"134 Stat. 266","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbc6660f3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbc6660f4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbc6660f5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Social Security Act, referred to in subsec. (a)(3)(A), (B)(ii)(III), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"act Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/620"},"text":"49 Stat. 620","children":[],"tail":". Titles II and XVI of the Act are classified generally to subchapters II (§ 401 et seq.) and XVI (§ 1381 et seq.), respectively, of chapter 7 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1305"},"text":"section 1305 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act, referred to in subsec. (b)(2)(F), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/128"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–128","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/1425"},"text":"128 Stat. 1425","children":[],"tail":". Title I of the Act is classified generally to subchapter I (§ 3111 et seq.) of chapter 32 of Title 29, Labor. For complete classifica